{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Give all Kinship Carers statutory parental leave.",
        "additional_details": "Give all kinship carers up to 52 weeks statutory \u2018kinship leave\u2019 when their children come into their care. 52 weeks would be in line with maternity and adoption leave, and allow kinship carers the to settle with the children they care for, who are some of the most vulnerable in our society, and have suffered, abuse, neglect, domestic violence or parental bereavement to end up in kinship care. Studies show children fair better in kinship care than in the care system, let\u2019s make the system fairer.",
        "background": "There are an estimated over 250,000 children in the UK living with friends and family (kinship Carers) as they can no longer live with their birth parents.\r\n\r\nKinship carers take on the role of parent at very short notice and are not entitled to any parental leave under the law.",
